PyPassword Generator
A simple Python password generator that creates randomized passwords based on user‑selected counts of letters, symbols, and numbers. The script uses Python’s  module to assemble a secure, shuffled password with customizable complexity.
Features
• 	Lets the user choose:
• 	Number of letters
• 	Number of symbols
• 	Number of numbers
• 	Randomly selects characters from predefined lists
• 	Shuffles the final password to ensure randomness
• 	Outputs a fully randomized password every run
How It Works
1. 	The script asks the user how many letters, symbols, and numbers they want.
2. 	It randomly selects characters using .
3. 	All characters are combined into a single string.
4. 	The final password is shuffled and printed.
